On Dec 17, 2004, at 11:04 AM, Neal354(-at-)wmconnect.com wrote:

> on a 76 vw camper the passenger seat how does it swivel ? also their 
> is a
> large metal disk under the seat what does this do. the seat are out of 
> the bus
> and im not sure i have all the parts

The disk is the swivel piece; it bolts down to the pedestal, and 
presses down on the rail piece.  A lever from the rail piece locks into 
a slot cut in the disk.

(I think I have that right... I thought I took photos of my swivel 
setup when I did my seat restoration, but alas, I did not.)

